<br>
Get a hold of a set of Mechanical Lock Picks from a good gnome tinker. They're easy to make, and I only paid the cost of the lockpick kit (required to make the item). They raise your skil by 2 percent. This means that when you cap your skill to 200 at level 39, you'll be able to open all the 201 or higher doors... in other words, any door in Norrath.<br>
There's also a pair of gloves that drop in Maiden that will have a similar boost to your lockpick skill, but the mechanical kit is safer, easier to get, and more certain too... the gloves might not drop, but the gnome can make the kit from readily available items.<br>
Note that any door you can successfully open will have a chance to increase your lockpick skill. I hit 200 on the lower door in Befallen. Some doors just do it faster than others. <p><html><center><a href="mailto:danny.butcher@verizon.net">I'm a mail link! Click me!</a></center><center><a href="mailto:danny.butcher@verizon.net"><img src="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze2bj96/spidor.gif" border="0"></a> <center><i><b> (Redeemed) The world is what we make it; let's make it free. </b></i></center></html></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FFFF00>- </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/btheemeralddagger>Emerald Dagger</a><font color=#FFFF00> - </font><a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ftheemeralddaggerfrm1>General Rogue Discussion</a> <font color=#FFFF00> - </font><br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM GAMES AD SCRIPT -->
